text: Sozialistische Volkszeitung ('Socialist People's Newspaper') was a communist newspaper published from Frankfurt am Main, West Germany. It was an organ of the Communist Party of Germany. It was published daily (except Sundays) between August 1, 1949 and August 17, 1956. ==References== Category:German- language newspapers Category:Daily newspapers published in Germany Category:Communist newspapers Category:Communist Party of Germany Category:Mass media in Frankfurt
